Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.16,0:00:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.04,0:00:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting under a sky aglow with dusk,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,our little boat lingered onward dreamily.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Children three nestled near with eager eye and willing ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Long has paled that sunny sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.35,0:00:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The echoes of their laughter and the memories of our joy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.82,0:00:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,have all been slain by autumn frosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.95,0:01:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where has she gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,having rivaled the sun itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.12,0:01:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In a wonderland they lie, dreaming as the days go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.25,0:01:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreaming as the summers die.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.01,0:01:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever we drift down the stream, floating through its golden gleam.
